description:
&lt;p&gt;Exciting opportunity for a Specialist Intermediate Care Nurse, Band 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dorset HealthCare University Foundation Trust requires a Registered Nurse with Advanced Practice skills to work in their Intermediate Care Service based in Bournemouth. The role involves working as part of a dynamic multidisciplinary team managing patients with acute illness, preventing admission to hospital and supporting Discharge to Assess. There will be a requirement to participate in Consultant led MDT discussions, and case manage complex patients. A high level of skill is required to manage the risk of caring for acutely unwell patients in their own homes and supporting the multi-professional team with understanding nursing needs for this group of patients. Clinical support, CPD and supervision will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will also be expected to manage staff including professionals not from nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is for 37.5 hours per week and includes shift working as the service operates 365 days a year 08.00 - 20.00. There is a need to use your car to visit patients in their own homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you enjoy working in a multi-professional team in a fast paced service, making autonomous decisions about patient care then please apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check. The DBS levies a charge of £40 and the Trust will recover this cost in instalments from your first 3 salary payments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants who subscribe to the DBS update service and are able to present a valid DBS certificate will not incur a charge&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are interested in moving to Dorset we also offer a generous relocation package of up to £5,000. For further details on relocation expenses please email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;dhc.careers@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
